---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../../components/Breadcrumbs.astro';
import CTABlock from '../../components/CTABlock.astro';
import BlogHero from '../../components/BlogHero.astro';
import BlogFigure from '../../components/BlogFigure.astro';
import RelatedPosts from '../../components/RelatedPosts.astro';
import { business, BASE } from '../../data/business';
import { postBySlug, postsBySlugs, RELATED_POSTS } from '../../data/posts';

const post = postBySlug('composite-deck-build-ayrshire')!;
const relatedPosts = postsBySlugs(RELATED_POSTS[post.slug] ?? []).slice(0, 3);
const siteUrl = business.siteUrl.replace(/\/$/, '');
const url = `${siteUrl}/blog/${post.slug}/`;
const ogImage = `${siteUrl}${BASE}/gallery/ayrshire-composite-deck-build-14-1600w.jpg`;

const articleSchema = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'Article',
  '@id': `${url}#article`,
  headline: post.title,
  description: post.description,
  inLanguage: 'en-GB',
  datePublished: post.date,
  dateModified: post.date,
  author: { '@type': 'Person', name: post.author, worksFor: { '@id': `${siteUrl}/#business` } },
  publisher: { '@id': `${siteUrl}/#business` },
  image: [ogImage],
  mainEntityOfPage: url,
  keywords: [post.keyword],
  wordCount: post.wordCount,
};
---
<BaseLayout
  title={`${post.title} | Sorn Handyman Services`}
  description={post.description}
  canonicalPath={`/blog/${post.slug}/`}
  ogImage={ogImage}
  ogType="article"
  extraSchema={articleSchema}
>
  <Breadcrumbs trail={[
    { name: 'Home', href: `${BASE}/` },
    { name: 'Blog', href: `${BASE}/blog/` },
    { name: post.title },
  ]} />

  <article class="container-x py-10 lg:py-14 max-w-3xl">
    <header>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-amber-600">
        <span>{post.area}</span>
        <span aria-hidden class="text-navy-900/20">·</span>
        <span class="text-navy-900/60">{post.readMinutes} min read</span>
        <span aria-hidden class="text-navy-900/20">·</span>
        <time datetime={post.date} class="text-navy-900/60">{post.dateDisplay}</time>
      </div>
      <h1 class="mt-4 font-serif text-4xl md:text-5xl font-black text-navy-900 leading-tight">
        {post.title}
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-5 text-lg text-navy-900/75">
        A new composite deck in an Ayrshire back garden for a repeat customer.
        Materials supplied, frame built, boards laid and the edges trimmed
        square. A low-maintenance finish that is ready to use straight away.
      </p>
    </header>

    <BlogHero slug="ayrshire-composite-deck-build-14" />

    <div class="prose-sorn mt-8 text-lg cv-auto">
      <h2>What the job involved</h2>
      <p>
        We set out the footprint on a fresh sub-base, then built a
        pressure-treated joist frame on concrete pads with positive falls so
        water runs away from the house. Joist centres were set to the board
        manufacturer's spec, not eyeballed — composite is less forgiving than
        timber if the frame is too open.
      </p>
      <p>
        Boards were laid with hidden clips for a clean top surface, expansion
        gaps left at every end, and the perimeter finished with colour-matched
        fascia boards. A proper composite deck should look tidy from the
        garden, from the path and from above.
      </p>

      <BlogFigure slug="ayrshire-composite-deck-build-14" />

      <h2>Things to think about before you start</h2>
      <p>
        Composite sits higher than you think once the frame is underneath, so
        plan door thresholds and step heights before you buy a single board. If
        the deck is going against the house, the top surface must sit well
        below the DPC — 150mm is the usual line. Getting that wrong bounces
        water at your wall.
      </p>
      <p>
        Colour in the brochure rarely matches colour in the garden. Ask for an
        off-cut to sit out for a day in the spot the deck will go. Morning
        light, afternoon shade and a bit of wet weather all change how a
        composite board reads, and it is a lot easier to swap the sample than
        the whole deck.
      </p>

      <p>
        If you are in Ayrshire and need something similar, Fraser will come
        and look for free. Call <strong>07900 255876</strong> or WhatsApp
        <strong>+44 7472 223323</strong>. FREE no-obligation quote, every job
        priced individually.
      </p>

      <div class="not-prose mt-10 rounded-2xl border border-navy-900/10 bg-navy-50/50 p-6">
        <p class="text-sm text-navy-900/60">Written by</p>
        <p class="mt-1 font-serif text-xl font-bold text-navy-900">{post.author}</p>
        <p class="mt-2 text-navy-900/75 text-sm">{post.authorBio}</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>

  {relatedPosts.length > 0 && (
    <RelatedPosts posts={relatedPosts} eyebrow="Keep reading" heading="Related posts" variant="tinted" />
  )}

  <CTABlock
    heading="Planning a deck this year?"
    sub="Send a photo of the garden and we will come and have a proper look."
    location="Ayrshire"
  />
</BaseLayout>
